'''Larkya La''' is one of the longest pass in Nepal [[Himalayas|Himalaya]], situated at 5125 m above the sea level<ref>{{cite news|title=Larkya Main, Georgians claim first ascent in Himalaya|url=http://www.planetmountain.com/en/news/alpinism/larkya-main-georgians-claim-first-ascent-in-himalaya.html|accessdate=7 February 2018|agency=Planet Mountain|issue=17.11.2017}}</ref>.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://nepalitimes.com/news.php?id=17686#.WnsUXOhuZPY|title=Crossing the Larkya La|last=COWAN|first=SAM|date=|website=http://nepalitimes.com|archive-url=|archive-date=February 7, 2018|dead-url=|access-date=February 7, 2018}}</ref> It locates in between [[Dharmashala, Kannur|Dharmasala]] and Bhimtang when trekkers would be doing Around [[Manaslu]] Trek<ref>{{cite web|last1=Aryal|first1=Rakesh|title=Manaslu Circuit Trek Itinerary|url=https://www.aroundmanaslutrek.com/manaslu-circuit-trek-itinerary/|website=Around Manaslu Trek|publisher=Manaslu Trekker}}</ref>.

