'''Stockholm Partnerships for Sustainable Cities''' is an [[organization]] which gathers and disseminates information and technology developed through [[Sustainable urbanism
|sustainability]] projects in several countries. The organization attempts to help representatives of national and [[local government]]s, [[industry]], [[non-governmental organization]]s, academia, [[Broadcast media|media]], [[financial institution|finance institutions]], and [[international organization]]s to share their knowledge and experience in [[applied technology]] and management. 

The group focuses on the respective roles of industry, local government, and communities in sustainable [[urban development]], and how these roles evolve and influence each other.

