'''Winship Point''' ({{coord|62|15|S|58|44|W|display=inline,title}}) is a point at the west side of the entrance to [[Potter Cove]], [[King George Island (Antarctica)|King George Island]], in the [[South Shetland Islands]]. Named by the [[United Kingdom Antarctic Place-Names Committee]] (UK-APC) in 1960 for [[Jonathan Winship]], master of the ship O'Cain in 1820-21, operating from Potter Cove.

